<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1918,2017]" pageId="3" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1918,1945]" pageId="3" pageNumber="278">Description.</emphasis>
Vertex yellowish brown, with large black patch in middle of anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1171,1271,1918,1945]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[163,1420,535,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,525,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Seriana bacilla sp. nov.—1 Habitus, dorsal view; 2 Habitus, lateral view; 3 Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4 Face; Empoascanara (E) gracilis Dworakowska, 1992—5 Habitus, dorsal view; 6 Habitus, lateral view; 7 Head and thorax, dorsal view; 8 Face; Tautoneura (T.) mayarami Mathew &amp; Ramakrishnan, 1996—9 Habitus, dorsal view; 10 Habitus, lateral view; 11 Head and thorax, dorsal view; 12 Face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3621191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3621191/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="278">Figs 5, 7</figureCitation>
). Eyes greyish black (
<figureCitation box="[227,330,1954,1981]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[163,1420,535,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,525,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Seriana bacilla sp. nov.—1 Habitus, dorsal view; 2 Habitus, lateral view; 3 Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4 Face; Empoascanara (E) gracilis Dworakowska, 1992—5 Habitus, dorsal view; 6 Habitus, lateral view; 7 Head and thorax, dorsal view; 8 Face; Tautoneura (T.) mayarami Mathew &amp; Ramakrishnan, 1996—9 Habitus, dorsal view; 10 Habitus, lateral view; 11 Head and thorax, dorsal view; 12 Face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3621191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3621191/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="278">Figs 5, 7</figureCitation>
). Pronotum yellowish brown, with median and lower half black brown (
<figureCitation box="[1147,1249,1954,1981]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[163,1420,535,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,525,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Seriana bacilla sp. nov.—1 Habitus, dorsal view; 2 Habitus, lateral view; 3 Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4 Face; Empoascanara (E) gracilis Dworakowska, 1992—5 Habitus, dorsal view; 6 Habitus, lateral view; 7 Head and thorax, dorsal view; 8 Face; Tautoneura (T.) mayarami Mathew &amp; Ramakrishnan, 1996—9 Habitus, dorsal view; 10 Habitus, lateral view; 11 Head and thorax, dorsal view; 12 Face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3621191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3621191/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="278">Figs 5, 7</figureCitation>
). Scutellum yellowish brown, basal triangles black; scutellar suture obvious (
<figureCitation box="[843,943,1990,2017]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[163,1420,535,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,525,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Seriana bacilla sp. nov.—1 Habitus, dorsal view; 2 Habitus, lateral view; 3 Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4 Face; Empoascanara (E) gracilis Dworakowska, 1992—5 Habitus, dorsal view; 6 Habitus, lateral view; 7 Head and thorax, dorsal view; 8 Face; Tautoneura (T.) mayarami Mathew &amp; Ramakrishnan, 1996—9 Habitus, dorsal view; 10 Habitus, lateral view; 11 Head and thorax, dorsal view; 12 Face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3621191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3621191/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="278">Figs 5, 7</figureCitation>
). Forewing semitransparent, brownish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,153,504]" box="[199,1101,153,179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">
Abdominal apodemes small, not exceeding hind margin of 4rd sternite (
<figureCitation box="[1004,1088,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[169,1411,525,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[164,1423,525,1865]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Empoascanara (E) gracilis Dworakowska, 1992—22 Abdominal apodemes; 23 Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 24 Subgenital plate; 25 Style; 26 Aedeagus, ventral view; 27 Apical part of aedeagal shaft, ventral view; 28 Aedeagus, lateral view; 29 Connective; 30 Pygofer dorsal appendage." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3621195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3621195/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,153,504]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,375,188,215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer lobe broad; pygofer dorsal appendage bifurcate near middle, with dorsal branch short and ventral branch long (
<figureCitation box="[425,507,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[169,1411,525,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[164,1423,525,1865]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Empoascanara (E) gracilis Dworakowska, 1992—22 Abdominal apodemes; 23 Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 24 Subgenital plate; 25 Style; 26 Aedeagus, ventral view; 27 Apical part of aedeagal shaft, ventral view; 28 Aedeagus, lateral view; 29 Connective; 30 Pygofer dorsal appendage." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3621195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3621195/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate broadened sub-basally, provided with 3 long macrosetae on lateral surface, numerous peg-like setae and microsetae along dorsal margian and near apex (
<figureCitation box="[1092,1175,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[169,1411,525,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[164,1423,525,1865]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Empoascanara (E) gracilis Dworakowska, 1992—22 Abdominal apodemes; 23 Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 24 Subgenital plate; 25 Style; 26 Aedeagus, ventral view; 27 Apical part of aedeagal shaft, ventral view; 28 Aedeagus, lateral view; 29 Connective; 30 Pygofer dorsal appendage." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3621195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3621195/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Style truncate at apex, preapical lobe distinct (
<figureCitation box="[411,495,296,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[169,1411,525,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[164,1423,525,1865]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Empoascanara (E) gracilis Dworakowska, 1992—22 Abdominal apodemes; 23 Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 24 Subgenital plate; 25 Style; 26 Aedeagus, ventral view; 27 Apical part of aedeagal shaft, ventral view; 28 Aedeagus, lateral view; 29 Connective; 30 Pygofer dorsal appendage." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3621195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3621195/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus shaft curved dorsad, serrated along upper half margins, with pair of long basal atrial processes; gonopore located at lower half length of shaft on ventral view. Preatrium and dorsal apodeme larger in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[391,518,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[169,1411,525,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[164,1423,525,1865]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Empoascanara (E) gracilis Dworakowska, 1992—22 Abdominal apodemes; 23 Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 24 Subgenital plate; 25 Style; 26 Aedeagus, ventral view; 27 Apical part of aedeagal shaft, ventral view; 28 Aedeagus, lateral view; 29 Connective; 30 Pygofer dorsal appendage." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3621195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3621195/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Figs 26, 28</figureCitation>
). Connective nearly Y-shaped, with distinct central lobe and short arms (
<figureCitation box="[1311,1393,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–30" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[169,1411,525,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[164,1423,525,1865]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 22–30. Empoascanara (E) gracilis Dworakowska, 1992—22 Abdominal apodemes; 23 Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 24 Subgenital plate; 25 Style; 26 Aedeagus, ventral view; 27 Apical part of aedeagal shaft, ventral view; 28 Aedeagus, lateral view; 29 Connective; 30 Pygofer dorsal appendage." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3621195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3621195/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="279">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
